name: Persian tiger
description:
From the collection "inside: Lost things"

I'm extinct
Like Persian tigers
And my smile is disappearing
And the warmth of my hands
I've been hunted
And my soul hangs on wall of your house
Like the skin of Persian tigers
And my mind
sits on the ledge of your room
And watches you in the arms of others
I'm extinct
And my heart
Like an Iranian tiger
No worries about mating
I do not like any heart from anywhere in the world
China, India, America, Australia!
it does not matter...
 There is no woman in love after me
I am latest generation of women in love
And my gaze will take the last moment of love with it
I am the last
Like Persian tigers
The last lover
The last woman
The last person who really loved you ...

for the last Persian tiger...and you...
